          "body": "### Term Label\n\nperimenopausal\n\n### Definition\n\nThe  
  transition phase before menopause, characterized by a drop in estrogen and  
  symptoms like irregular periods, hot flashes, and mood swings. This phase   
  can last from a few months to as long as 4 years.\n\n### Definition         
  citation\n\nhttps://www.healthline.com/health/menopause/difference-         
  perimenopause\n\n### Synonyms\n\nperimenopause || peri-menopause || peri-   
  menopausal\n\n### Parent term\n\nEFO:0001272 adult\n\n### Child terms\n\n_No
