  ## Summary                                                                  
                                                                              
  Added new EFO term **EFO_****0920060 "perimenopausal"** to src/ontology/efo-
  edit.owl as requested in issue #2653                                        
  https://github.com/EBISPOT/efo/issues/2653.                                 
                                                                              
  ### Term details:                                                           
                                                                              
  • **ID**: EFO_0920060                                                       
  • **Label**: perimenopausal                                                 
  • **Definition**: "The transitional phase before menopause, characterized by
  declining and fluctuating estrogen levels and associated symptoms such as   
  irregular menstrual periods, hot flashes, night sweats, and mood changes.   
  This phase typically begins several years before menopause and ends with the
  last menstrual period."                                                     
  • **Parent**: EFO:0001272 (adult) — sibling to EFO:0002721 (postmenopausal) 
  as requested                                                                
  • **Synonyms**:                                                             
      • perimenopause (hasExactSynonym)                                       
      • peri-menopause (hasRelatedSynonym)                                    
      • peri-menopausal (hasRelatedSynonym)                                   
  • **Cross-references**: HP:0040406 (Human Phenotype Ontology), NCIt:C15692  
  (NCI Thesaurus)                                                             
  • **Definition references**: PMID:41836925, PMID:41829913, PMID:41807917    
  (all 3 PMIDs provided in the issue, all verified as relevant perimenopause  
  literature)

